            {
                "s2_paper_id": "b238e76cc1724d25bf859977919cb4e6d3201c61",
                "title": "The Zika virus: Lurking behind the COVID\u201019 pandemic?",
                "year": 2020,
                "venue": "Journal of Clinical Pharmacy and Therapeutics",
                "citation_count": 20,
                "reference_count": 83,
                "abstract": "The sudden and extensive outbreak of coronavirus (SARS\u2010CoV\u20102) has overshadowed another developing viral threat: the Zika flavivirus. Of particular concern is that pregnant women can pass Zika virus to the foetus, and there is a strong implication of an association between Zika virus infection and foetal microcephaly. Currently, there is no vaccine, and there is no cure.",
